    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Minimal local fix                                                           
                                                                                
    The quickest change that stops the crash is to eliminate the premature      
    free(b->name) in the error path of load_blob:                               
                                                                                
                                                                                
     static blob_t *load_blob(const char *name) {                               
         blob_t *b = malloc(sizeof(blob_t));                                    
         if (!b) return 0;                                                      
         b->name = strdup(name);                                                
         if (!b->name) {               /* out‑of‑memory */                      
             free(b);                                                           
             return 0;                                                          
         } else {                                                               
             /* Recoverable error: keep the name, just report size == 0 */      
             b->size = 0;                                                       
             return b;                 /* do NOT free(b->name) here */          
         }                                                                      
         /* The following two lines are now unreachable, but are kept for       
     clarity */                                                                 
         b->size = strlen(b->name);                                             
         return b;                                                              
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Effect: The name buffer remains owned by the returned blob_t. The sole      
    place that frees it is destroy_blob, so it is freed exactly once.           
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    More thorough root‑cause fix                                                
                                                                                
    A deeper, safer redesign would avoid returning a partially‑initialized      
    blob from a function that has already encountered an unrecoverable          
    condition:                                                                  
                                                                                
                                                                                
     /* Revised load_blob */                                                    
     static blob_t *load_blob(const char *name) {                               
         blob_t *b = malloc(sizeof(blob_t));                                    
         if (!b) return NULL;                     /* allocation failure */      
         b->name = strdup(name);                                                
         if (!b->name) {                           /* OOM */                    
             free(b);                                                           
             return NULL;                                                       
         }                                                                      
                                                                                
         /* Normal path – compute size */                                       
         b->size = strlen(name);                                                
         return b;                                                              
                                                                                
         /* -----  Recoverable error handling  ----- */                         
         /* If you truly need to signal a recoverable error without             
            leaking resources, you can return NULL (or an error code) */        
     }                                                                          
                                                                                
                                                                                
    And update the caller to respect a NULL return value:                       
                                                                                
                                                                                
     blob_t *b = load_blob("abcdef");                                           
     if (!b) {                                                                  
         fprintf(stderr, "load_blob failed\n");                                 
         /* no need to call destroy_blob */                                     
         exit(EXIT_FAILURE);                                                    
     }                                                                          
     destroy_blob(b);                                                           
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Why this is better:                                                         
                                                                                
     • No object is returned in an inconsistent state.                          
     • All resources allocated inside load_blob are released only once, either  
       on normal exit or on explicit error handling.                            
     • The double‑free pathway disappears entirely, eliminating the crash.      
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Summary                                                                     
                                                                                
    Root cause: load_blob frees b->name while still returning the blob_t *,     
    and later destroy_blob frees the same pointer again → double free →         
    “Deallocation of freed memory”.                                             
                                                                                
    Minimal fix: Remove the stray free(b->name) (or return NULL instead of the  
    partially‑initialized blob) so that destroy_blob is the exclusive free      
    point.                                                                      
                                                                                
    Thorough fix: Refactor the error handling to return NULL (or an error       
    indicator) and keep memory ownership semantics clean, ensuring each         
    allocated resource has a single, well‑defined release point.                
                                                                                
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------  
                                                                                
    Recommendation                                                              
                                                                                
    Fix the code as follows:                                                    
                                                                                
                                                                                
     -         free(b->name);      /* release the name buffer */                
     -         b->size = 0;                                                     
     -         return b;           /* hand the partially-initialised blob       
     back */                                                                    
     +        /* On recoverable error simply return NULL or keep the name */    
     +        /* without freeing it; the caller will free it exactly once */    
     +        b->size = 0;                                                      
     +        return b;   /* keep name intact until destroy_blob */             
                                                                                
                                                                                
    Or, for a more robust design, make load_blob return NULL on any error and   
    let the caller handle cleanup, ensuring no object is returned in an         
    inconsistent state.                                                         
                                                                                
                                                                                
